President Trump and Vice President Pence participated in a tree planting ceremony on the South Lawn of the White House to celebrate Earth Day and National Park Week. They discussed the importance of environmental stewardship and the reopening of national parks and public lands for the American people to enjoy. The Vice President also emphasized the need to prioritize mental health during the ongoing coronavirus crisis. The First Lady and Second Lady also made remarks about the significance of the tree planting and mental health awareness.